==Old English==
===Etymology 1===
From Germanic ''*ixwa-, *iwa-'', from Indo-European ''*ek̑u̯os'' ‘horse’.  Cognate with Old High German [[eha-]] (in personal names), Old Norse [[jór]].  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[equus]], Avestan ''aspa-'', Tocharian A ''yuk'' B ''yakwe'', Baltic ''*ečwā-'' (Lithuanian [[ašva|ašvà]]), Old Irish [[ech]] (Irish [[each]]).

